Section K CTAN Edition

Welcome to the XML based and XSL generated version of The TeX Catalogue Online, Section K CTAN Edition. This is a listing of entries in the TeX Catalogue and may take a little time to load, but is hopefully worth it. Have a look at the Catalogue Preface for alternative ways of accessing the catalogue.

The TeX Catalogue Online is also available from any CTAN node or mirror, including the following. Pick one that is close to you. (The "search" link attempts to find a CTAN node that may be close to you, courtesy of Randy Kobes. Multiple clicks may find alternatives.)

Icons associated with many entries in the catalogue allow you to:

  • view the directory on CTAN
  • view documentation (possibly many)
  • view documentation in PDF format (requires the acroread plugin)
  • jump to the package's home page
  • download a gzip'd tar file from a nearby CTAN node (not supported by all nodes)
  • download a gzip'd tar file from ftp.dante.de

Other icons simply provide further information about the package:

  • part of the teTeX distribution
  • available on the TeX Live CD ROM

The license type, version (if known), and the date of the last change made to each particular Catalogue entry are also provided.

kix No caption.
Implements KIX codes as used by the Dutch PTT for bulk mail addressing. (Royal Mail 4 State Code.) KIX is a registered trade mark of PTT Post Holdings B. V.
license: unknown (1998/09/19)
kluwer No caption.
A LaTeX2e class file for submissions of journal articles to Kluwer Academic Publishers, Dordrecht, the Netherlands.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
knst No caption.
A package supporting the generation and correction of multiple option tests as appears in TUGBoat Volume 17, Number3: ``Fast and secure multiple option tests''.
license: unknown (1996/10/21)
knuth No caption.
Knuth's own documentation, including the TeX book and the MetaFont book.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
koi8 No caption.
A package to perform internal translation from the KOI-8 encoding (de-facto standard of the UNIX world) to the so called ``alternative encoding'' used by most Cyrillic packages. You still need one of these packages for the actual Russian typesetting. The style works with all major Cyrillic packages: cmcyr, cmcyralt , LH . See also rawprint
license: lppl (1999/03/03)
koma-script No caption.
A drop-in replacement for the article/report/book classes with emphasis on European rules of typography and paper formats as laid downTschichold/01/by. The article class, for example, becomes scrartcl.
license: nosell (1998/11/30)
kpathsea Path searching library for TeX-related files.
license: lgpl (1999/03/03)
kuvio Drawing macros and fonts for diagrams.
license: lppl (1999/03/03)
